data.title: Ali Wentworth
data.text:
1315 31st St NW

Washington, DC

Ali Wentworth (b. January 12, 1965) is a comic, writer and actress who has appeared in such films as Jerry Maguire, The Love Bug and It's Complicated. She's also had numerous television appearances, including stints on Seinfeld and The Oprah Winfrey Show and co-hosting the program Living It Up! With Ali & Jack with Jack Ford. Wentworth is married to ABC News journalist and former Clinton Administration advisor George Stephanopoulous, with whom she has two children. Prior to moving to New York for the ABC job, the couple lived in this 5-bedroom estate in Washington, DC, located at 1315 31st St NW, which was on the market in 2010 for a reported $6.35 million.

Who else lived here?
